00:03:54.476 --> 00:03:57.678
show up everywhere in WordPress,

00:03:57.913 --> 00:04:02.117
in content writing,
image creation, chatbots,

00:04:02.517 --> 00:04:05.554
search, and even layouts.

00:04:05.887 --> 00:04:08.723
AI is really, really powerful.

00:04:09.057 --> 00:04:11.993
I think we all can agree to that,

00:04:12.327 --> 00:04:15.096
and exciting at the same time.

00:04:15.797 --> 00:04:19.968
But power without care
can really push people out.

00:04:21.102 --> 00:04:24.972
The heart of this session
is just one simple question.

00:04:24.973 --> 00:04:29.678
As we automate more,
are we including everyone,

00:04:30.111 --> 00:04:33.615
or are we quietly leaving
some people behind?

00:04:34.683 --> 00:04:37.885
I'll use plain English, real stories,

00:04:37.886 --> 00:04:42.123
and steps that we can use
right away moving forward.

00:04:42.457 --> 00:04:48.129
My goal is that we all leave
here feeling confident,

00:04:48.496 --> 00:04:54.336
and a little
more protective of our user.

00:04:58.373 --> 00:05:01.576
Why this talk really matters?

00:05:02.177 --> 00:05:05.271
Let's start with the word
accessibility.

00:05:06.181 --> 00:05:12.286
Accessibility means that everyone
can use what we build,

00:05:12.487 --> 00:05:15.724
including people who are blind,

00:05:16.057 --> 00:05:21.496
those who have low vision,
deaf, or hard of hearing,

00:05:21.830 --> 00:05:24.227
people with limited mobility,

00:05:24.366 --> 00:05:26.267
people with speech differences,

00:05:26.268 --> 00:05:29.236
and people who process
information differently,

00:05:29.237 --> 00:05:33.875
like ADHD, autism, or brain injury.

00:05:34.442 --> 00:05:39.361
There are over a billion people
in the world with disabilities.

00:05:40.315 --> 00:05:42.381
That's not a small group.

00:05:44.119 --> 00:05:46.588
Many of us, at some point,

00:05:46.921 --> 00:05:51.205
temporarily or permanently,
will rely on accessibility.

00:05:51.726 --> 00:05:55.463
Maybe you break a wrist
and can't use a mouse.

00:05:55.797 --> 00:05:59.701
Maybe you're in a noisy
cafe and need captions.

00:06:00.035 --> 00:06:02.836
Maybe your eyes
are tired at midnight,

00:06:02.837 --> 00:06:07.309
and you need clear text
and big buttons.

00:06:08.410 --> 00:06:09.750
Now add AI.

00:06:10.130 --> 00:06:12.647
AI is writing our posts,

00:06:13.081 --> 00:06:17.786
drafting our emails,
picking our images,

00:06:18.119 --> 00:06:22.691
as well as answering
our users at 2:00 AM.

00:06:23.024 --> 00:06:25.159
If we don't design with everyone

00:06:25.160 --> 00:06:28.229
in mind, AI can speed up exclusion.

00:06:28.763 --> 00:06:30.497
Not because we are bad people,

00:06:30.498 --> 00:06:34.369
but because we didn't slow
down to notice.

00:06:34.936 --> 00:06:39.538
Now today we slow down,
we notice, and we improve together.

00:06:41.076 --> 00:06:44.279
I'll use a few terms during the talk.

00:06:45.213 --> 00:06:47.881
AI is artificial intelligence.

00:06:47.882 --> 00:06:49.917
This is the tech that predicts,

00:06:49.918 --> 00:06:53.188
generates, and recognizes patterns.

00:06:53.521 --> 00:06:55.870
LLM, large language model,

00:06:55.871 --> 00:06:59.361
is the brain
behind many writing tools.

00:06:59.794 --> 00:07:04.899
WCAG is Web Content
Accessibility Guideline.

00:07:05.500 --> 00:07:11.439
This is our global rulebook
for making the web work for everyone.

00:07:11.973 --> 00:07:18.546
ARIA stands for Accessible
Rich Internet Applications.

00:07:19.347 --> 00:07:22.650
Labels and roles
that help screen readers

00:07:22.984 --> 00:07:26.287
understand complex widgets.

00:07:26.621 --> 00:07:31.459
NVDA for Windows and VoiceOver
for Apple as screen readers.

00:07:31.993 --> 00:07:35.058
These are softwares
that read the screen out loud

00:07:35.059 --> 00:07:38.233
and let people
navigate without signs.

00:07:38.566 --> 00:07:41.395
ASR, Automatic Speech Recognition,

00:07:41.396 --> 00:07:42.969
this is speech-to-text.

00:07:42.970 --> 00:07:45.240
TTS is text-to-speech.

00:07:45.874 --> 00:07:49.444
I'll explain this naturally as we go.

00:07:50.245 --> 00:07:53.148
If a term sounds scary, don't worry,

00:07:53.481 --> 00:07:56.885
I'll keep it simple
and very practical.

00:07:59.452 --> 00:08:01.435
Who gets left out?

00:08:02.157 --> 00:08:04.459
When automation moves fast,

00:08:04.893 --> 00:08:08.963
who's being left out
or being left behind?

00:08:09.330 --> 00:08:11.999
Now imagine a blind student

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:16.304
relying on VoiceOver
to read course pages,

00:08:16.871 --> 00:08:19.406
a deaf parent trying to catch

00:08:19.407 --> 00:08:22.777
a school announcement
without captions,

00:08:23.378 --> 00:08:27.582
and a person with stutter
asking a chatbot for help

00:08:27.916 --> 00:08:34.189
and always getting, "Sorry,
I didn't catch that," again and again.

00:08:35.390 --> 00:08:39.994
A shopper who uses only
a keyboard and is stuck

00:08:40.328 --> 00:08:42.559
in a pop-up with no escape.

00:08:43.698 --> 00:08:50.638
A new English speaker facing
a wall of long and formal AI texts.

00:08:51.239 --> 00:08:53.408
These are not edge cases.

00:08:53.441 --> 00:08:55.376
These are our users.

00:08:55.877 --> 00:09:00.248
These are us
at different time of our lives.

00:09:01.149 --> 00:09:04.284
Accessibility,
I believe, isn't charity.

00:09:04.285 --> 00:09:08.790
It's just good design
and basic respect.

00:09:10.058 --> 00:09:12.593
I want to tell you a very short story

00:09:12.594 --> 00:09:17.565
to why I really relate to this.

00:09:18.099 --> 00:09:21.202
A friend of mine, she's blind,

00:09:21.536 --> 00:09:24.429
was applying for a community grant.

00:09:24.739 --> 00:09:30.211
A shiny AI chatbot auto-launched
and stole the screen focus.

00:09:30.812 --> 00:09:35.334
Her screen reader could not reach
the form fields anymore.

00:09:35.517 --> 00:09:37.197
She tried and tried.

00:09:37.218 --> 00:09:38.418
Then she said,

00:09:38.419 --> 00:09:42.703
"I feel like the internet
is not built for me anymore."

00:09:43.191 --> 00:09:46.027
That sentence changed me.

00:09:46.361 --> 00:09:47.427
I'm a developer.

00:09:47.428 --> 00:09:51.799
I can ship features,
but can I ship belonging?

00:09:52.133 --> 00:09:53.835
Can I ship calm?

00:09:54.168 --> 00:09:57.105
Can I ship an experience that says,

00:09:57.438 --> 00:10:01.576
"You're welcome here
exactly as you are?"

00:10:01.943 --> 00:10:03.477
That's why I care.

00:10:03.478 --> 00:10:07.315
That's why I'm here
with you today for this talk.

00:10:09.183 --> 00:10:11.119
Where AI breaks,

00:10:11.653 --> 00:10:15.857
let me name a few pain
points with you right now.

00:10:16.190 --> 00:10:20.595
In voice and chat,
a search struggles with accents,

00:10:21.296 --> 00:10:25.300
stutter and soft voices,
as well as loud speeches.

00:10:25.967 --> 00:10:29.102
It keeps saying, "Sorry,
I didn't get that."

00:10:29.103 --> 00:10:30.783
That becomes a wall.

00:10:30.939 --> 00:10:36.010
In images, AI generators
make really, really beautiful images.

00:10:37.845 --> 00:10:44.652
Often forgets alt text,
which is alternative text for images.

00:10:44.986 --> 00:10:50.758
That's a short description
of images that screen readers need.

00:10:52.627 --> 00:10:56.206
In writings, LLMs love

00:10:56.207 --> 00:10:59.801
long, long sentences
and very big words.

00:11:00.134 --> 00:11:04.656
For many readers, simple
is kind and complex is a barrier.

00:11:04.973 --> 00:11:09.910
When it comes to keyboard,
AI-made pop-up can trap

00:11:09.911 --> 00:11:13.281
the tab focus, tab key.

00:11:13.915 --> 00:11:16.517
Then now the focus disappears.

00:11:16.851 --> 00:11:20.088
The close button is now unreachable.

00:11:21.189 --> 00:11:23.223
When it comes to data bias,

00:11:23.224 --> 00:11:27.494
now if training data
rarely includes disability

00:11:27.495 --> 00:11:29.364
or global diversity,

00:11:29.697 --> 00:11:34.035
AI keeps to ignore
those patterns over and over.

00:11:34.736 --> 00:11:37.171
These are not rare bugs.

00:11:37.772 --> 00:11:40.672
They are common patterns we can fix.

00:11:44.278 --> 00:11:48.316
WordPress powers over 40% of the web.

00:11:49.017 --> 00:11:51.019
That's amazing.

00:11:54.188 --> 00:11:58.426
It also means our choices are scale.

00:12:00.395 --> 00:12:04.095
AI is arriving in SEOs,

00:12:04.535 --> 00:12:07.669
helpers, writing assistants,

00:12:08.736 --> 00:12:13.808
image tools, chart widgets,
and layout generators.

00:12:14.676 --> 00:12:19.547
If a plugin forgets alt
text or keyboard focus,

00:12:19.881 --> 00:12:25.153
that mistake travels to thousands
and thousands of sites.

00:12:26.320 --> 00:12:29.756
The flip side is beautiful.

00:12:33.428 --> 00:12:36.798
If a plugin does accessibility well,

00:12:37.131 --> 00:12:41.269
that goodness spreads just as fast.

00:12:42.336 --> 00:12:45.205
We have a chance to lead the open web

00:12:45.206 --> 00:12:51.646
toward automation that is human,
careful, and kind.

00:12:54.649 --> 00:12:57.585
There are top fail patterns I see.

00:12:57.919 --> 00:13:02.290
One is no semantic HTML.

00:13:02.924 --> 00:13:06.042
Pages built with random divs instead

00:13:06.043 --> 00:13:09.731
of real headings,
lists, and landmarks.

00:13:10.264 --> 00:13:13.367
Screen readers
can't map the structure.

00:13:14.068 --> 00:13:18.206
Two is low color contrast.

00:13:19.340 --> 00:13:22.877
Elegant gray on gray may look modern,

00:13:23.211 --> 00:13:27.048
but it's unreadable for many.

00:13:27.582 --> 00:13:32.153
Then the other one is missing
ARIA labels and roles.

00:13:33.020 --> 00:13:35.822
Complex widgets
with no roles or names,

00:13:35.823 --> 00:13:38.893
assistive tech can't announce them.

00:13:40.061 --> 00:13:44.365
Then we have the keyboard
traps and lost focus.

00:13:47.735 --> 00:13:51.372
Modals open, or rather,
Pop-ups open and focus vanishes.

00:13:51.706 --> 00:13:54.442
Escape doesn't close anymore.

00:13:54.776 --> 00:13:57.011
Focus doesn't return.

00:13:57.378 --> 00:13:59.213
No captions, as well,

00:13:59.480 --> 00:14:03.606
is the other example,
no captions and transcriptions.

00:14:04.585 --> 00:14:11.192
Videos and audios stay silent
to deaf or hard of hearing users.

00:14:15.163 --> 00:14:18.575
I can say none
of this is really mysterious.

00:14:19.033 --> 00:14:22.637
It's just work
we must remember to do.

00:14:27.575 --> 00:14:28.776
Now,

00:14:29.477 --> 00:14:35.082
yes, I want to give
you examples we can really look at.

00:14:35.416 --> 00:14:38.352
Now let's imagine three quick scenes.

00:14:38.686 --> 00:14:41.189
One is the hero image.

00:14:42.657 --> 00:14:47.928
You use an AI tool
to create a hero image,

00:14:48.095 --> 00:14:51.865
a girl painting a mural
without an alt text,

00:14:51.866 --> 00:14:56.663
and a blind user hears "image.jpg".

00:14:59.207 --> 00:15:01.008
With alt text,

00:15:01.776 --> 00:15:06.013
it says "a smiling girl
paints a bright school

00:15:06.047 --> 00:15:10.785
mural with blue and yellow colors."

00:15:11.352 --> 00:15:16.557
Suddenly, now the moment is shared.

00:15:18.092 --> 00:15:22.396
Scene two, the formal paragraph.

00:15:23.064 --> 00:15:29.837
AI writes commands,
"The onboarding procedure".

00:15:30.371 --> 00:15:33.006
Then you change it to,
"Start setting up."

00:15:33.007 --> 00:15:36.077
Fewer words, feels more welcoming.

00:15:37.712 --> 00:15:40.981
Then the third
one is now the chat trap,

00:15:40.982 --> 00:15:44.352
like I mentioned with my friend.

00:15:44.819 --> 00:15:48.823
A chat widget opens
when the page loads.

00:15:49.457 --> 00:15:52.426
Tab can't reach the close button.

00:15:53.160 --> 00:15:56.175
Keyboard users
are stuck at that point.

00:15:56.530 --> 00:15:58.609
Now you add focus management,

00:15:58.610 --> 00:16:03.104
send focus into the dialogue,
escape closes it.

00:16:03.671 --> 00:16:05.351
When it closes it,

00:16:05.506 --> 00:16:08.842
return focuses
to the button that opened it.

00:16:08.843 --> 00:16:11.240
Now it feels more respectful,

00:16:11.479 --> 00:16:16.817
and more easy for those people
who are using the keyboard.

00:16:18.419 --> 00:16:20.402
Small changes, I can say

00:16:20.688 --> 00:16:25.058
it's now showing big
dignity at this point,

00:16:25.059 --> 00:16:27.995
the changes
that we are talking about.

00:16:29.597 --> 00:16:32.099
Simple and reliable fixes.

00:16:34.101 --> 00:16:37.605
Five fixes carry so much weight.

00:16:37.939 --> 00:16:43.311
One is alt text with meaning,
not just logo or images.

00:16:43.711 --> 00:16:47.214
Paint the picture
in a short sentence.

00:16:47.748 --> 00:16:52.987
Then plain language,
short sentences, everyday words,

00:16:53.988 --> 00:16:59.126
headings, and bullets
as well to make things simpler.

00:17:00.394 --> 00:17:05.299
Then the semantic HTML,
so real buttons for buttons,

00:17:05.633 --> 00:17:10.371
and real links for links.

00:17:10.738 --> 00:17:15.075
Use headings in order
just to make sure

00:17:15.076 --> 00:17:17.544
that everything is in flow,

00:17:17.545 --> 00:17:20.580
and things like screen
readers can understand

00:17:20.581 --> 00:17:23.985
that will be read aloud to the users.

00:17:24.318 --> 00:17:29.757
The other thing is managing focus.

00:17:31.659 --> 00:17:34.552
Now this is focus rules for modals.

00:17:34.662 --> 00:17:38.833
Move focus in,
keep the tab key inside,

00:17:39.166 --> 00:17:44.338
and then escape closes,
return focuses back.

00:17:44.939 --> 00:17:48.075
Keep visible focus outline as well.

00:17:48.409 --> 00:17:51.946
The other one is caption
and transcriptions.

00:17:53.280 --> 00:17:57.318
Auto-captions are a start,
but edit them,

00:17:57.651 --> 00:18:00.855
provide transcripts
for audio as well.

00:18:01.489 --> 00:18:08.062
If we all do these five things,

00:18:08.396 --> 00:18:15.169
you remove so much
friction from so many lives.

00:18:17.838 --> 00:18:22.676
Tools that help us make sure
that we are doing this.

00:18:23.010 --> 00:18:27.114
Use tools to catch what AI misses.

00:18:27.448 --> 00:18:31.058
WAVE and axe DevTools,

00:18:31.438 --> 00:18:36.824
these are... flag missing labels,

00:18:37.158 --> 00:18:40.252
contrast issues,
and structure problems.

00:18:40.394 --> 00:18:45.399
Then there's Chrome Lighthouse,
gives quick checks.

00:18:46.200 --> 00:18:51.805
NVDA in Windows and VoiceOver
on Mac or iPhone lets you feel

00:18:51.806 --> 00:18:55.743
the page like a blind user.

00:18:56.310 --> 00:19:00.281
Then there's Hemingway
and other readability

00:19:01.115 --> 00:19:04.285
tools that help
you simplify LLM text.

00:19:04.919 --> 00:19:07.398
Then there's contrast checkers

00:19:09.011 --> 00:19:15.162
to keep color contrast at all times.

00:19:15.629 --> 00:19:19.533
You run this regularly, and remember,

00:19:19.867 --> 00:19:24.038
tools assist,
but us as humans decide.

00:19:26.207 --> 00:19:29.310
