00:20:17.858 --> 00:20:19.527
Standard guides,

00:20:21.762 --> 00:20:25.565
WCAG, Web Content
Accessibility Guideline,

00:20:25.566 --> 00:20:28.402
is now our compass at this point.

00:20:28.736 --> 00:20:33.407
Its core idea is POUR: perceivable,

00:20:33.874 --> 00:20:36.944
operable, understandable, robust.

00:20:37.711 --> 00:20:41.315
For perceivable, can people sense it?

00:20:41.649 --> 00:20:42.427
No.

00:20:42.428 --> 00:20:47.588
Things like alt text,
contrasts, captions.

00:20:47.939 --> 00:20:50.857
Operable, can people actually use it?

00:20:50.858 --> 00:20:54.394
These are keyboard access,
no traps, enough time.

00:20:54.395 --> 00:20:59.094
Understandable, can people
follow it using plain language,

00:20:59.095 --> 00:21:00.775
consistent patterns?

00:21:01.202 --> 00:21:05.172
Then, for robust,
does it work with assistive tech?

00:21:07.208 --> 00:21:11.412
You don't have to memorize
the whole spec,

00:21:11.745 --> 00:21:15.540
but you can start with the low levels

00:21:15.541 --> 00:21:19.787
like A and AA basics.

00:21:20.487 --> 00:21:23.924
